cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.AI 

The paper deals with automated emotion recognition from facial images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a multi-task learning approach, which involves training a model to perform multiple related tasks simultaneously. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from data. Additionally, the paper deals with emotion recognition, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (HCI), suggesting that it could belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are a subset of artificial intelligence (AI), suggesting that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with multiple datasets, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
